caption: One of my favorite vegan spots when I come to D.c. area .I recommend the general chicken with rice with a side side & apple spice kombucha.
This restaurant gives fantastic service and delicious food. The best restaurant around town. The food and drinks came out rapidly and the prices were fair. Highly recommended.
Expensive for no reason
Food was good and hit the spot!
If you are into plant based eating,  trust me this should be your spot

Terrible, terrible, terrible service.  We had to go back three times for our takeout order - first because they forgot our order, second because they gave us the wrong order, third because one of the bowls was spilling out and leaking through the bag.  The food was fine but not worth an extra 30 minutes of time to get it.

We are a large family, of vegetarians, who have a soft spot for Asian dishes. I am glad places like this exist. They get an A+ for colorful effort in presentation. It is hard to thrive in a pandemic and they are faring well. It should be said though that they lack in the area of flavor, more specifically their dishes all taste the same, and two out of two for things missing in my order that I was not bothered to go back and fix. The French fries were good, but it’s not going to remain on my active list. You may be thinking “Then why did you go twice?”. Gift certificate 🌼

I want to eat here everyday, food is AMAZING and prices are hekka reasonable (especially for The City!) Took my very carnivorous bestie here and even she was impressed. Those trolley fries with fried "chicken" on top and that Japanese katsu 🤤🥰 Yes please!
Love the concept. The vegan General Tsos is delicious as well as the vegan pork. Looking forward to trying more options
This place is a great meal if you are tired of cooking. Especially if you have dietary restrictions!
My first time ordering from Pow Pow. Everything was delicious and flavorful. It was a little bit too spicy for my daughter,  so next time I'll ask them to make her dish mild.

This was my first time ordering from here and I am newly vegan. Not to mention, I am a very picky eater 😅. The food was delicious😋!! Very well seasoned and fresh. I had the sesame chicken salad and rice bowl, Thai pumpkin soup and miso soup. I can’t wait to try other items on the menu.
Such an amazing place. I'll eat at PowPow every time I'm in the area. Very accommodating to allergen and nut-free diets.

Open for COVID carry out. Delicious food with healthy options and guilty pleasures. Friendly staff and an engaged owner who creates a consistent quality menu with rotating food specials.  Lastly it is nice to have a complete vegan menu. Would recommend and will continue to support.

If I could give this place more stars, I absolutely would. The food here is always amazing. I highly recommend the firecracker fingers—I literally could eat these every single day for the rest of my life.
I love their chicken so much. The texture and flavors are superb. I have many other things I have left to try!
This was my first time ordering from Pow Pow and I was very pleased with my dish! The General’s Chicken was flavorful and the dessert egg roll was delicious!! I highly recommend.

I would highly recommend Pow Pow!! I got the K-town BBQ bowl and it was incredible! It was honestly one of the best, if not the best vegan meal I've ever gotten. It had so much flavor and the fake chicken was SO good. I also added jackfruit on top and it was absolutely delicious! The bowl was really large, and easily could have been 2 meals. If you're ever in DC, you have to check out this place!!!
Incredible flavor in every bite. This plant based spot will definitely make your taste buds very happy. I had the Fire Cracker Chicken Bowl and will be coming back to try out the rest of the menu.
You kidding me? Too good for words. I am not vegan but this place slays. You wouldn't even know that it's vegan. So much flavor. Long live Pow Pow.

This has become a regular for us. Delicious plant-based food that is reliably delicious. Prompt, friendly service. Many dairy free and vegan options and the menu is well labeled. Open for curbside pick-up!

Love this place.  Such an interesting yet yummy menu.  It’s eclectic and comfort food all in one.  It’s also plant based which is a huge plus, having recently moved into the ‘hood and seeking non-meat options.   The fries are amazing and the Thai pumpkin soup could be served in any fine dining restaurant.

I have yet to go into the restaurant, however, I have them delivered at least once a week. Food doesn't make you feel as if its vegan. I recommend the dumplings, and general tso chicken with half salad and rice.

PowPow is the Asian fusion spot every vegan/vegetarian/plant-based person needs. Husband loves the general tso’s and Natalie porkman. The pumpkin soup is FIRE, so rich you won’t believe there’s no dairy in there. The cashew mozzarella croquettes are good but somewhat hit or miss. My only critique is I wish they offered a more extensive GF menu. Jackfruit, black beans, etc don’t compare to having a plant-based meat option!
Update: Back again. Food is so unique and flavorful.  Delicious plant based bowls. Filling and creative.
My all-time favorite vegan fast food restaurant. The menu is great and they always change it up. Servers are super friendly and accommodating.
I love the general tso bowl and the choo choo chips (regular fries) are fresh cut and so good! I have become a regular here.
Certainly a spot worth stopping by, the food is excellent and well prepared, the pricing is reasonable and it is consistently well organized in here. Keep it up.
The food is good the service is terrible. The staff don’t know how to speak to people without an attitude and snark remarks. If you really want to eat here order delivery.
I tried the Taiwanese Fried Mozzarella Croquettes for the first time today they are so good, it's a must try. I also love the Yoga Dragon Bowl,  The Purity Bowl and the Trolley Fries

I think I wrote about this place before. However, it's just that good. To be honest if you are vegan or not this place is for you. I tasted just about everything on the menu now. My favorite is the mom style fried rice, Tokyo Roboto general's chicken, yoga dragon and purity bowl. I know that's a lot. I love the appetizers as well. I can't call it. The only thing is parking. Before covid-19 it was hard to get parking on the street from Friday night and Saturday night. Sunday through Thursday is okay. Try this place. You will not be disappointed if you love wholesome food. You definitely get your money worth. Also try insomnia cookies which is down the street from Pow Pow.
Great food at a great price

MAN! I wanted to love this place! I love Asian food and live a plant based lifestyle. Ordered a lot of food for the whole family (and because I was anxious to try so many different things). Most things I ordered were good! The Taiwanese Fried Buffalo Mozzarella, excellent! The Chimi Chimi dessert egg roll, DELICIOUS! The General’s Chicken, good but mine had a hair in it. I called and they did reverse the charge for it, AFTER asking me to inspect the hair and tell them the color of the hair, which threw me because my stomach turns at the very THOUGHT of hair in food. That was a bummer. Lost my appetite for the rest of the night. All in all, the food that I did get to try was good. Minus two stars for the hair and the way it was handled although I do appreciate the refund since I did not eat it.

Pow Pow is one of my favorite vegan restaurants in the city. It never disappoints. Highly recommend the generals chicken, the egg rolls and the buffalo or orange chicken fingers. If you can order a buffalo chicken sandwich on Monday, it will blow your mind. Everything I’ve ordered at pow pow has truly been wonderful.
Love the total vegetarian easy to eat bowls. Take out is a breeze and groceries are great.

PowPow was one of the first places I ordered for delivery in quarantine and I was so impressed! First, I have to admit I'm kind of a skimmer when it comes to reading details and I honestly did not know this place is all veggie. I ordered the Sichuan Dumplings, Pow-Tine, and Fried Chicken Fried Rice.  The Pow-Tine arrived safely vented to avoid getting soggy (kudos to the GrubHub driver) and was my favorite of all the dishes. I love this Asian take on poutine. The dumplings did arrive a bit soggy but that's to be expected. If you refry them a little, they crisp up easily. Dumplings were also pretty tasty. The chicken fried rice was interesting. Again, I failed to realize that this would be fake chicken and I'm not really a fan of fake chicken so I wasn't crazy with the texture. But, it was hearty and once I thought of it more like tofu was fine.
The food is amazing. Best vegan restaurant
Food was solid.  Order was missing an item.

First time I came here, I hated it. I must have gotten the wrong thing because second time was the charm here. I had the wings, the poutine and the asian pumpkin soup. All were super delicious. The wings were mindblowingly good. Sorry to ever have doubted you and glad I gave it a second shot. I would love to see the menu get a little bigger to try some more yummy vegan things. Also love that you guys are randomly kosher. I grew up in a kosher house-hold.

All I can say is wow! What an awesome meal! The Bubbie’s Buffalo Fried Chicken Sandwich was sooooo good! The heat was perfect and the blue cheese made it right. As always the Trolley Fries were amazing and made it the perfect lunch combo for me. Great job to the whole crew at Pow Pow for taking care of the DMV lunch and dinner needs. You guys ROCK! 🤘🏼🤘🏼
PowPow is more or less a religion for me. And, as such, I pray that they survive this plague and reopen upon its cessation. Stay strong, PowPow. I need you.
Reuben egg roll is delicious!
HORRIBLE
This place is incredible. Come here if you want consistent quality in every order!
The food was excellent, I got mock chicken fried rice. The problem I had was the wait time and when I got my food it was cold.
Went in hungry. Left satisfied.
Wouldn't believe it was vegan if I want made aware. Will be back!
I love it here!
Very nice atmosphere! The food was nice and comforting! Excellent flavor!

(Translated by Google) Super good, only vegetarian choices. The drinks are excellent and the service is quick. A good address in Washington for sure !!  (Original) Super bon, que des choix végétariens. Les boissons sont excellentes et le service est rapide. Une bonne adresse à Washington pour sur !!

Very tasty, vegan, food!! The staff was friendly and very helpful. I loved the Natalie Porkman and the Trolley Fries. For the quality and location, expect the food to be a little on the pricey side. The flavors would totally make you want to do it again. Parking, like all of DC, was limited but again, worth it!

Happy vegan! I can not explain how amazing the food was. I visited on 24 January 2020 and it was my first time there. The firecracker fingers had me thinking they were real chicken (been vegan for 4 years) and I checked with the women preparing the food and she confirmed it but dang, it was close to what I remember chicken tasting and the texture being like.  I had the firecracker fingers, Yoga Dragon and the dessert, the Chimi Chimi Pow Pow Egg Roll. Definitely worth a trip here if you’re visiting the area and want tasty, hearty vegan food.

My daughter & I chanced upon Pow Pow on a recent trip to DC. I Had the Yoga Dragon & Onion Poppers.  The Dragon was good. Filling, extreemely  fresh and flavorful.  But it wasn't what I ordered,  so be sure to pay attention to the clerk because this place is not fast food. The Onion Poppers were terrible & I would not recommend them. It looked as if they cut the root ends off green onions,  dipped them in batter and fried them. They were tough and bitter.  Basically inedible & I threw them away. Cute place.  Interesting menu Everything was clean
Great food! Service was a bit off at first, but food was really good.
Today was my first time.  I didn't know what to expect. No meat 😳. The teriyaki chicken was delicious. The employees were pleasant.

I was looking forward to trying a new vegan restaurant but was very disappointed after receiving my order. The egg roll was very oily, drenching two napkins. The filling was delicious and the egg roll as stuffed full but the wrapper itself was inedible.  I also ordered the General Chicken. It did not look or taste fresh. I do not believe it was freshly made. I was unable to finish the meal. Everything was very salty. I will not be returning to this restaurant.
I had the Purity without tomatoes and it was so good. This was my first time here. I liked it so much that I started looking on Google maps to see if there was another one closer to me.
Good Lord this was delicious.
The Trolley Fries were so good. Can’t wait to come back and try everything on the menu
Friendly staff
Taste is great (brilliant) but they don't give a lot of the veggie chicken/pork, they give too much rice and vegetables. They should correct the imbalance.

Not Worth The Money #1. Been contemplating on trying out this spot due to the mixture of reviews, & the negative reviews are accurate. Ordered the Trolley Fries, Disco Egg Rolls, & chicken fried rice.  Fries are Basic point blank. Disco egg rolls taste like they were taken out of a freezer & flash fried. Fried rice was decent , but the chicken was very bland!. Not going there again.
I went for the first time today and the food was great. Staff was very patient with me while I tried to figure out exactly what I wanted to try. Love this place
OMG! Now this is what you call Vegan Cuisine! So good I didn’t even get to take a pic! Vegan or not you’ll enjoy!

This is my new favorite place.  Food is so good, especially the dynamite fingers (just make sure to get the sauce on the side, dont get it tossed, makes it soggy, better on the side - trust me).  My only complaint is that the staff always waits for you while waiting for you to fill out the tip.  Feel like this is a pricey enough fast casual and a tip shouldn't be expected everytime (I probably give it every 4 out of 5 times I go, but also dont want to feel obligated)
Overpriced and not very good.

I haven’t eaten in here but I have ordered from it 3 times now. Every time the food is amazing!! I’ve also had a couple of issues with the delivery drivers and had to phone the restaurant and they were so helpful on the phone both times. The Pow-Tine is my favourite and I love the firecracker fingers too. I could eat the food every day I think! And I’m a meat eater!
First time here. Great food, Great atmosphere.

Food is not that good it's not worth the price. Also I stepped in this place just to get out of the rain one day cause I had no umbrella and one of the employees kicked me and said if you not buying anything you have to leave. I was angry but I just left. I wasn't expecting to stand in there for 20 just about 10 minutes till I felt comfortable enough to go back in the rain because it was raining rather hard. I have spent money in here before and it just goes to show when you support these Asian businesses that they don't want nothing but money every time you see them otherwise they don't want to be bothered. Will never spend money here again and the food is not even worth it.

My fiancé and I love this restaurant! Everything is cooked fantastically and tastes divine! We would highly recommend. We ordered the Natalie Porkman and Yoga Dragon. Also tried Sichuan Dumplings (steamed) and the Taiwanese Fried Buffalo Mozzarella.
I really thought I was eating chicken but it was plant based. Amazingly delicious. Loved it will go again asap. Thanks .

I love their food! Favorite item on the menu is the Yoga Dragon. Due to their popularity you must come here and be prepared to wait a bit for the food to be ready (I’d say 2 out of 3 times). After all, its made fresh and they only have so many employees they can fit in their kitchen. Perhaps a second location would solve that problem.

This food is delicious! I am an avid carnivore however this restaurant blew me away with how delicious and unique its menu is. The cheese balls taste like creamy melty cheese and I could not believe it was vegan cheese. There has obviously been a lot of work that has gone into the menu at pow pow! I urge all vegetarians or vegans, or even omnivores to go try out this delicious place!
Awesome vegan food. I definitely left full with leftovers. Will be going back on my next visit to DC

All of their combos are good. I love the rice. And the drinks are delicious. The food sometimes tastes a bit processed, but that's the case with most casual cuisine. And, I love supporting meat and dairy free restaurants, so it's a win all around.
Great food, Nice service, worth it.

This place is EXCELLENT! First time here and as a DC native, I am glad we have something of this variety here :) the food doesn't taste "vegan" - it tastes GREAT! Highly recommend the general chicken bowl
Excellent all vegan restaurant. One of my favs
Food is fantastic! Great service!!
This place was incredible. Generous portions of delicious, plant-based foods. We'll absolutely be coming back here.
The food is amazing!!!!

My daughter and I traveled out of our way to try Pow Pow because of all the rave reviews. First I will say that the food we were able to order was delicious and the people who worked there were super friendly. Customer service was awesome. But I had a few issues. First, I ordered the Natalie Porkman but they were out of seitan but they switched the chikn for it. Second, I ordered the fried mozzarella but they were out of it and the truck was due the next day. Third, I wanted to try the banana egg roll dessert which I paid for but found out they were out of that too. So, three of the items I wanted to try were not in stock which was very disappointing being that we traveled a long way to try this place and our visit is over tomorrow. They did substitute another menu item for the banana egg roll which was nice. The only reason I would go back is because what we did order was very good and the employees were awesome. I will however call ahead to see if they are fully stocked. Otherwise I will not go out of my way.  Update: Customer service goes a long way in my book. I appreciate the fact that this is a small business and they make everything  in house. That's why I wanted to try it all! Because they were so awesome and because they took the time to reply to this review and because the food I did get was delicious....I will be back when I am in DC. Save a chimi chimi pow pow egg roll and some Taiwanese fried mozzarella for me please 😁

THE BEST VEGAN FOOD I HAVE EVER HAD. I really love Washington D.C. , have been there twice now. And the last time I came for holidays with my girlfriend we stayed super close to Pow Pow. Nearly every day we went there either for lunch or dinner and we loved every thing we tried and tried nearly everything. The only thing I unfortunately missed is the miso soup. The place is still run by the owner and his wife (who came up with this genius plant based stuff). And I really have nothing to complain about. Even bought the last 'Pow Pow' shirt they had.  Wish I found something similar close to were I life in Germany now.  If you have the chance , try it.
Food was fantastic and service was good.
First time eating here as we are from WV and food to die for!! AMAZING good!!! Dumplings are the best ive ever had in my life!!
it great food here
(Translated by Google) Niiiice  (Original) Niiiice
Great taste, good selection.  Will be a regular
A new twist on traditional dishes. Everything was exceptional including the house-made sauces!

I'm an omnivore with a love for meat, and the plant based meats at Pow Pow did not disappoint. The service was friendly, and the food was flavorful and delicious - the chicken substitute actually tastes and chews like chicken.  Highly recommend trying the sesame chicken fingers, the disco stick egg roll, and the miso soup (flavor was great, but should've been served hotter). Overall great and unique fast casual restaurant.
Nice Vegan place.

This is a must stop vegan hot spot! Wether you'd like them eat clean and healthy, or whether you are vegan or veggie and are looking for a good meal or some fast eats on H st, Pow Pow is a must! Every dish I've tried has been delectable. My favorite dish is the General Tso's, the flavor is incredible. I personally do not live the grilled chx options, as they are not as flavorful. The Trolly Chips (aka loaded fries) are 🤩. Eat here soon, you won't regret it!
Customer service is bad. They constantly make mistakes on order and be prepared for a long wait! The staff seems incompetent and show little care for customers time!
Deep fried tasteless appetizers.  I have been to many vegan restaurants but this one was awful.  Don't bother coming here.

The eggrolls stand up to their reputation hearty and delicious.. A great experience ! I wanted to try more but they closed without warning and I was turned away at the register promptly at 9pm before they started to dismantle. However, that won't  stop me from returning. Next time I'll start  earlier and order all at once.

Gave it a try, never again. A lot going on just to make it taste good. The Trolley fries were very soggy with all the toppings on it. The Pork Sword was so greasy, made me sick a little. On the side note, saw a lady working the food line dropped a spoon on the floor and continue to use it. hmmmmph.  Response to the owner... sorry, I am a little late on writing this review. Should have wrote it then. Has it been 2 years ago? Will definitely stop by again.

This is my first time going in, not getting delivery. Everyone there was very nice. Food is great, and my favorite is the mozzarella balls! I LOVE them! I also love everything is plant based so you know whatever you order will be vegan friendly... and of course delicious. I do wish they had another dessert option, but this food is truly delish. The drinks on the side are super refreshing, I got the ginger peach and could not get enough of it, it was so good!... sorry, no pics of the motz balls, I ate them already :)

This fast-casual book on H St is small, with limited seating (mostly counterside high top stools) but the food is hugely good. I've never had fries like the trolley fries before -- topped with kimchi and a mayo sauce and dried seaweed. It sounds quirky but all the flavors work so well together. But they're most famous for their giant egg roll, which is as thick as an arm and exactly the kind of greasy food you're craving when you order an egg roll. It's listed as a starter but it's really a whole meal.  The General's Chicken imitates the original so well, but my favorite entree is the Natalie Porkman, and not just for the bad pun. It's crispy and crunchy like fried chicken should be, with just enough sweet & sour sauce. And the Taiwanese fried cheese balls are as decadent as they sound. They also usually have a few rotating specials.  Basically, I've never had anything bad here. I'm sure if Pow Pow were located somewhere more central, it'd have an even bigger cult following. In the meantime, it's becoming my go-go delivery spot.

If you like vegan food you will love it here! The staff is friendly. The food is tasty. The core menus does not change but the specials are great. The fried onion popers are one of my favorites and the Disco Stick egg roll is enough for a whole meal if you get it large. Love that pineapple kimchi! You can drive and try to find a parking spot or just take the dc streetcar. Its free for now!
Is the meatless craze a fad? Well, I can't speak to that, but I can say this is a great place to partake!

Dishes are unique, creative and always delicious, prices are decent for the amount of food you get and service is generally pretty good. only complaint would be that the broccoli is usually overcooked and turns a little brownish green.
Love these vegan bowls!
They're one of the first to make really good plant-based food for everyone to enjoy. Love all of the dishes here and the creativity of the owners!
All I can say is yummy! Please make nutrition information available.

Phenomenal!!! Everything I have tried I have loved. Texture, seasoning, freshness...all fantastic. Sharkey is pretty awesome too. I bring all my friends (vegan and not vegan) here and they all love it.
A restuarant that is more than rice, veggies and bowl but a place to get a good quick meal with family and friends.
Excellent food and delicious fake meat. Excited for their all vegan menu in May.
Excellent tasty food. My wife and I shared the purity bowl on half and half (salad, rice mixture).
Plant based deliciousness!
This spot made my change my mind on vegan food ...for the better...the flavors are amazing
Amazing!
I enjoyed this space because all menu options are Vegan. I found that the menu is soy and gluten heavy. There is at least one option for most dietary restrictions.

First the positive, we got the trolley fries and the top ones were tasty but as we went deeper, the ones at the bottom were soggy. That was the only good, the grilled broccoli tasted like someone threw in a bottle of cologne. The rice has no flavour, the fried rice was soggy and the spicy sauce was very generously ladled which was very uncomfortable. The cashier was also kinda rude.  Not likely to return!

Friendly staff, and delicious General's Chicken dish! The Pumpkin Pumpkin soup was hearty and seemed to warm me from the inside out. My husband ordered the Mom's Fried Rice, and we both shared it; just as yummy as the General's Chicken! They also had different types of soft drinks that are all plant-based. The best-tasting one was the Mexican cola. I highly recommend this place. I was very pleasantly surprised.
Quick counter service. Great soup, good varied food options. Spicy available.
Amazing vegan options! The rice with the Wu-Banger was also slightly coconut flavored, a very welcome surprise.
Delicious food- always fresh! You would have never guessed it was all plant-based! I would eat here everyday if I could. Highly recommend checking this place out!
Great food. Party in my mouth!
I had my first bowl and it was soooo good. I can't wait to go back to try more items.

I was excited to try this vegan spot, I think their brand is refreshing. I got a bowl, the Wu Banger, and it first it was very good! The chicken tasted just like Chicken, but after a while it was too much for me. I’m not a big fan of food that tastes like meat. The food didn’t sit well with me or my friends afterwards. but I’m glad I tried it. It was a new and refreshing experience.

Protein-heavy vegan meals with delicious salad and sauce combinations modeled on American-Chinese food. Their coconut rice blend can't be beat. The Disco egg roll will turn heads from H street (it literally did when I ordered this for the first time). I recommend Natalie Porkman with a cherry kombucha -- tastes like a sour beer. Dreamy.  Oh, and the people watching is half the fun of dining here!
Great food..we loved it #eatpowpow... I will definitely be back soon!
Food was filling they have tasty miso soup which is unlimited and everything was vegan

Absolutely delicious. The regular size roll is a meal of it's own...and you won't regret it. The bowls are also great and have appeased the spicy eaters and no spicy eaters equally. They usually have some fun/funky special as well. This is my go-to when people visit from out of town or I'm having a rough week....or I just want something tasty.
Great food but beware of ordering take out - takes too long and they’ve never gotten my order right.
Fantastic vegan fast food!
Friendly staff, great selection of Asian fusion dishes, fresh ingredients, will visit again!
Tokyo roboto (pictured)- sweet service, delightfully satiating for a rainy evening - fusion, fusion, fusion!

Pow Pow's an incredible plant-based fast casual restaurant located on H street corridor, and their food is a must-try for vegans and meat-eaters alike!  They fuse different elements from Korean, Japanese, and Chinese cuisines to create delicious combos that’ll seriously impress.  They’re known for their beautiful bowls and massive egg rolls, but I recommend getting their trolley fries, their taiwanese fried mozzarella, and their firecracker fingers!  Happy eating, friends.

These guys screw up delivery more than any restaurant I've ordered from. They use GrubHub/Chownow and the order is either never delivered or you get the wrong thing. It's too bad too, because the food is excellent and vegan.
Amazing food and service. Vegan of course and tastes great.

Pow Pow never disappoints. I 1st tried them via delivery. SCORE! I was happy to see that their physical location was right on H St. SCORE ! The menu consists of meat free,  asian fusion dishes. Everything was prepped & prepared right in front of you in a.m open kitchen style. The staff is always friendly & patient while you decide & they have suggestions and recommendations waiting if you need it. They are willing to do modifications to menu items to accommodate their patron's tastes or dietary needs. It's always clean and bright inside. And usually not a long wait. Quick, clean, friendly... Pow Pow on H St.
Great vegan food! I've been there a few times and have yet to find something I don't like.
Excellent vegan fare, but can be slow when busy

Vegan Paradise full of flavor! I'm so glad Pow Pow went Vegan all the way since May with a variety of hearty dishes. Love the Yoda Bowl!  The Yoda Bowl is loaded with veggies with crunchy sriracha cashews that adds a nice kick, hearty grilled chicken mock meat coated in savory peanut sauce, and drizzle of creamy zesty cucumber lime sauce. Although I appreciate the variety of ingredients, the tomatoes and carrots didn't blend well together with black beans, edamame and the rice quinoa mix. I think mushrooms, broccoli, or corn would have been a better pairing. There's a seasonal bowl similar to the Yoda bowl, but with sweet potato instead of the mock meat, which I would try next time!  My meat-loving husband loved the crispy fried fingers smothered in sauce. I got 1/2 with the traditional firecracker sauce which is like a tangy buffalo sauce and other 1/2 with teriyaki sauce. I honestly couldn't taste the difference between the sauces. The only difference I could taste were the plain vs black sesame seeds. I enjoyed the sesame sauce. As the fried mock meat was doused in sauce, it had a very bold flavor that overpowered the Yoda Bowl. I love wings coated in sauce, but not to the point that the wings are swimming in sauce and leave little puddles as I pick them up. I recommend getting the sauce on the side.  I wasn't a fan of the Trolley Fries. I wanted to love the fries as they were loaded with my favorite ingredients (sriracha mayo, kimichi, scallians, ketchup), but the fries weren't crispy and lukewarm. Also the toppings were a bit of overload and sadly I ended up tossing out the entire tray of fries after a few bites.  Plenty of great choices and fun to try. Save your appetite for the Yoda Bowl!
Amazing food. How do they do it? Entirely plant based but you wouldn't know it wasn't fried chicken.

Pow Pow on H Street in Washington DC is a  vegan fusion restaurant that satisfies Kosher disciplines. It provides a satisfactory menu choice of imaginative and extremely tasty dishes, some hot and spicy. Other dishes like fries come with surprisingly embellished sauces. Yet others, like the mozzarella balls, are just an outright pleasant gastro surprise. Street parking, don't be put off by zip code. Good find.

Delicious! As a vegan I really appreciated what this place had going on. We were staying in Georgetown but it was definitely worth the trek out to this side of town. I loved everything except I would probably recommend skipping the cheese balls. The inside had more of a texture of mashed potatoes (but still taste pretty cheese like).
Healthy eating
Very clean and there food omg is to die for
Love!!!
Vegan yum yum for your tum tum. So good
Awesome Vegan Food specialist.

Ordered via Caviar and was so excited to try something new! All 3 - THREE - of us hated the food. (1 Italian 1 American and 1 Brazilian). Poor flavors, too spicey, SUPER oily. Just yuk. Disappointing considering the good reviews.
I'm a sucker for onomatopoeia, especially when the sound matches the flavor profile. It's like a sweet, delicious punch to the kisser. Muah!
Better than any Asian ford anywhere

This place is amazing!  I had to check it out once before bringing my wife, and loved it both times.  Do not miss the Giant Eggroll, but make sure you have someone you like with you to help pack it away, delicious and enormous!  The rice bowls are great, salad bowls are good too, but the 50/50 is the best.  And those Sriracha cashews, OMG!  Finally, topped it all off by sharing the dessert chimi with dairy free Nutella and banana, divine.  I can't say enough good things about the food at Pow Pow, except that to top it all off it is 100% plant based... I'm in love<3
Everything was superb. Fast casual, but as good as the vegan restaurants in New York.
Great food and great service. The Tokyo Roboto and Kimchi Brussel Sprouts are delicious!
Pretty good. Service took a lil bit tho
100% plantbase  and delicious!  you won't believe its vegan!

Disco Egg Roll was 11/10, Jackfruit BBQ bowl was huge portion and fresh veggies but jackfruit was pretty overpoweringly salty. Staff was incredibly friendly, would definitely go back. Hopefully other dishes aren't quite as salty. I'm not a vegetarian-loving guy, but this place exceeded my expectations.

Excellent. A diverse menu is available to choose Three of us ate here, each ordered a different dish, devoured our own, and were impressed by the others. We got a packed heavy dish for the price.  Pow pow loses a star for charging extra for being stingy about sauce. This place is excellent but nickel and dining diners for extra sauce (even extra sriracha) is just ridiculous.
Unbelievably delicious! More please.

I’m so excited for this place to be added to the slew of options on H street. A vegan/vegetarian Asian spot is literally all we have been missing. Obvi had to have the Natalie Portman on my first visit. I’m usually not a fan of tempeh or anything close to it but the flavor of this bowl threw me. It reminded me why I went vegetarian in the first place. So much flavor. The staff are amazing. Easily a Top 5 spot on the strip in my opinion
This place delivers exactly what you would expect it to be:  relatively cheap, tasty, greasy pan Asian Cuisine that happens to be all vegan.
Has parking space available.

I'm always excited to try a new vegan restaurant, especially since DC's vegan scene is so good. However, I found this spot incredibly disappointing. The main part of each dish, such as the mock meats and mozzarella balls, are quite delicious and have lovely sauces. However, they only use a tiny amount of sauce, not nearly enough for the dish. The vegetables are VERY bland to the point where they may even be unseasoned. I had to make a sauce at home to make half of the meal edible. And this is coming from someone whose diet consists of 80-90% vegetables!
For clarification, this is a vegetarian/vegan spot.
Big portions and super tasty!
Love this place❤
Flavorful, delicious food, and I'm so happy the menu is all vegan now!

I ended up there because I wanted Chinese and the only other option on H St was Major's carryout. And boy, was it the right decision! Their food is an Asian fusion from Korean, to Thai, Chinese and Japanese. Everything was flavor packed. I had the General's Chicken. The chicken texture was fantastic, crunchy outside and tender flaky inside. The sauce was the perfect amount and really good. Served on citrusy greens and coconut rice/quinoa, decorated with a line of sesame seeds and plated very beautifully in a biodegradable container. I also had to try the trolly fries. Sooo good! While you won't find any meat in their dishes, I don't think you'll really notice. They far surpassed my expectations for fast casual Asian food.
LOVE the food. Everything is delicious. Thank you!

Just stopped by for my 5th or 6th visit last night and had to share some love for his place. I’ve tried several of their dishes, Powtine fries and egg roll and have not been disappointed. Yoga Dragon is by far my favorite. I love that there are layers of flavor from different sauces and the large bowl is big enough that I have some left overs. I’m not a vegan but this place hits the spot (so happy they have fries). Only wish they were closer to Anacostia.

A dear friend of mine and myself visited yesterday and had a good time overall, however the food is another story. I had The General's Chicken and it was good, yet a bit spicier than I thought it would be and the broccoli was cold. My friend ordered the Wu Banger, which she wasn't a fan of at all, moreso due to the sauce. It was also very warm on the inside of the restaurant, which may have helped to attract the bugs flying around us as we're eating. The prices seemed adequate for the portion sizes. We had high hopes for this spot, but we will probably never visit again. The staff we're friendly and the restaurant was clean. Just and FYI there is NO SUSHI being served here, even though it was in the category of Sushi Restaurants when we looked into the spot to begin with!! You be the judge!!

(Translated by Google) We did not enjoy it at all. Food is not very tasty or too spicy. The boy ordered a burger that came as a vegetable and fruit salad inside a hamburger bun and hollow industrial fries. It was a pity for us to travel there.  (Original) לא נהנינו בכלל. אוכל לא טעים במיוחד או שחריף מידי. הילד הזמין המבורגר שהגיע כסלט ירקות ופירות בתוך לחמניית המבורגר וצ'יפס תעשייתי חלול. חבל היה לנו על הנסיעה עד לשם.
Food was awesome. Forgot it was vegan, definitely a pleasant surprise on the H Street corridor.

Great food! Was very surprised to find a prep began restaurant here. I'm from India so ik full well how good vegan food can taste and these guys did a great job! I gave 4 stars cause the kidd soup could've been better
I’m a big fan. Everything I’ve had is delicious. Staff are super friendly.

2/5 stars and im being generous here. Slow service when there was no one in front of us, the employees were just talking The food presentation made it actually look appealing and appetising but little did my stomach know, there was a storm to come. It did not sit well, me and my S/O felt flu sick as it felt like it sat in our throats and as soon as the 2nd bite hit my taste buds my tongue curled, a bad sour with a hint of how a horse stable smells. As a vegan this disheartens me horribly personally, we were looking forward to coming here for almost 2 weeks!.. Maybe it was just what I got the "Tokyo Roboto", It was so bland, the rice was gritty, and the pineapples had no apparent flavor but a greasy grilled taste. Also my boyfriend got The General's Chicken and unlike me he LOVES spicy but it was just too much, like it canceled all the flavor the bowl looked like it had to offer.. So take my review with a grain of salt, maybe it was just a bad day for the employees, short end of the straw for us ingredient wise. But 10/10 NOT worth the price because we weren't even able to stomach our whole bowls, leaving a wasteful total of 1 out of our 2 bowls in left overs...

I can't recommend this place enough. My girlfriend and I were deterred at first due to it being a vegan restaurant but left raving about how good the food was our entire trip. We got fries and a daily special and both were amazing. Please come to Indy!

Alright boys, another review. So, as a first timer to Pow Pow, I'm adjusting to the vegan diet and because of the area I reside in, getting here takes an hour roughly to reach. Majority of the places (vegan) my boyfriend and I have been to, have been really expensive. Pow Pow is a restaurant we've come across a couple of times but never explored it. Today, Sunday June 24, we decided to come in. I ordered "The General's Chicken" and my boyfriend ordered the "Tokyo Roboto". Immediately the flavors were bursting intensively, my bowl was sweet and spicy, while my boyfriend's was exceptional. Alas  that quickly changed  I noticed with our service our food sat out(before being transferred to a tray) before being called, and oddly enough our food quickly grew cold  but I had cold spots in my food, my broccoli was bland, and tasted frozen as if they bought it at the giant down the street. The rice was gritty and distasteful, I had a couple scallions in my bowl which tasted a little over cooked. I can handle spicy food, I seek after spicy dishes, so I'm not sure what is churning in my stomach. My boyfriend and I felt sick after our meal, he quickly moved to the restaurant bathroom, and I'm having pains. I can see good intentions in this small shop. For me, I'd really like to test the dessert but I'm too afraid to chance $5 on another dish here. I may return for the "Chicken Fingers", and "Taiwanese Friend Mozzarella" but until then I won't be recommending this place to anyone curious enough to try this restaurant.
Best vegetarian I've had!?

I went to pow pow for an event with a friend who is a vegetarian. I was pleasantly surprised that she had so many options she could choose from! I'm also lactose intolerant and their vegan fried mozzarella balls were so good!! They also have a seasonal egg roll that is basically a Thanksgiving dinner wrapped and fried, if that thing wasn't heaven I don't know what is! I wish this place was closer to me or to my office so I could go more often!
Reallyyyyy yummy, the chef is absolutely fantastic.  My only qualm is that there seems to be a lot of sodium, but if that's not something that bothers you than don't worry about it
Best meal I had ln DC.

Such an excellent veg/vegan spot! I had the sweet and sour pork dish and the seitan was super delicious, as was the sauce. Definitely recommend for anyone, not just vegans. Great comfort food and creative place.
Very good vegan food. Unique and pretty good prices.
Updated. Minus two stars for loss of all meat options (now vegan only). Fake chicken is pretty good,at but def not the same as real. Was favorite restaurant on H st.

Please note that as of May 2018, Pow Pow has changed to only serving vegan food. I want to really like this place, but can't. Food wise, the food is good and I can't taste the difference between meat. I'm taking off a star for the slow service I had. With six people in front of me, it took 15 minutes to get my food. I'm also taking off a star for the prices. Most of the items are about $2 more expensive than another Korean BBQ place a block away.
Great and clean food.

This place is STELLAR! Everything is vegan, without obnoxiously publicizing it. There are definitely meat options, but everything tastes and fills PERFECTLY. The specials are always fun. Try the mozzarella balls!  Sharkey is an absolute doll and I'm so glad he helped me find the perfect first dish to hook me.
Great place for vegan eats. The Natalie Porkman is the best faux pork I've ever had.

Some good vegan options, and the bowls are filling with lots of good side veggies. I would change a few details (chives, tomatoes etc. could be cut smaller, and I don't like the inclusion of peppers that aren't meant to actually be eaten) but overall a very solid meal.
This place is so incredibly good. From the bowls, to the eggrolls, to the chicken wings, to the iced coffee. EAT EVERYTHING.

An Asian fusion fast-casual restaurant with amazing plant-based options! I'm a fan of the meat substitutes on the menu (mock chicken and pork seitan) - they are marinated well with the sweet and savory sauces that come with the bowls. Paired with the combination of fresh vegetables and grilled fruits, the pork seitan is the star of the show. I believe Pow Pow has set the precedent for making meat substitutes the delicious go-to. I have tried the Chimi Chimi Pow Pow Egg Roll, Natalie Porkman, Yoga Dragon, and the Purity Bowl. They were all tasty and filling!
One of the most unique restaurants I've been to in DC. Amazing flavours, real fusion food. And the best part, anything can be made Vegan. Hope new branches open up soon!

Surprisingly good... I was worried because I dont like Korean food and definitely not kimchi. But I wanted to try the fries. Luckily they let me try the kimchi first. It didn't taste like the fermented kimchi I was expecting. More like a cross between onions and garlic. In short, the fries were great and I would have them again.  The chicken pineapple bowl mix is good if you are to stick with something on the healthy side. Very taste. I had the chimi chimi (banana Nutella eggroll)
I love pow pow. Always good. Always fresh. Always creative.

Great selection of vegan eats! So delicious. I can't wait to go back!  ***edit: I have since ordered delivery from Pow Pow numerous times with great success. I have been quite pleased with their delivery service.  I went back to the H street location and was disappointed to walk up to the door at 9:20 pm to find that they were closed. For a lunch/dinner spot that seemed a bit early to me for a Thursday night. I also thought it was strange that their hours are listed as Noon-close. What does that mean? Do they close at random times?
This is the best vegan food restaurants in Washington DC
You can never go wrong with the features of the day.........Fried Mozzarella Balls
Lil crowded at times but mostly open and on time
Light fulfilling meal.

Food not as good as pictures advertised. Nice clean and cozy space but the food is not good. The wings were extremely over cooked... the egg roll with steak was full of cheese and no other ingredients. Not a place I would return. The fountain drinks are the best part.

Flavors....flavors and more flavors. Mouth watering choices! Not your typical run of the mill restaurant. This is a must try for DC locals as well as visitors. great atmosphere, great employees, great food selection and did I mention flavors!?!? I hope they expand to more locations!
It takes a bit longer to get your food than you'd think but it's worth the wait! Delicious pork seitan.
It's great but really overpriced. Not the best Asian fusion either.
Loved the experience very helpful and food is on point.
Authentic and tasty cuisine
Soooooo good. This place is amazing, from the simple and seriously delicious food to the Maine root soda machine. Cool low key atmosphere and good prices. Highly recommended!

This is my favorite place for food in DC. I always take my friends here and they always love it. I had a great Thai pumpkin soup the other day. Their homemade seitan is so good. You don't even have to be Veggie to love it. All the sauces and food combinations have been specifically tested and made from hand by the owners, resulting in a great experience for your mouth. Not to mention it's healthy. I'm always coming here after 30-60 Mike bike rides to refuel. Five stars!!!

There's nothing more pleasant than being greeted with smiling faces of enthusiastic staff, when trying out ba new dining spot. I love the quirky decor, clean dining area, and mix of music. The staff were very helpful when it came to menu recommendations and even allowed us to taste a few of the signature sauces. When it comes to a healthy and tasty Asian fusion eatery, Pow Pow really packs a punch!

We hat a fun unique blend of flavors. If you are near this place I would highly recommend. This place is a must, i loved every bite and I wish I was in town longer because this place would be on my return list a few times.
Definitely a gem. They have great vegan options as well.

This place is a gem. One of the best places in DC. I am a vegetarian and hard to find a place like this with so many vegetarian options. This is wonderful! I got the Natalie Porkman. I highly recommended it. The trolley fries where so different I am not big on space but it was the perfect amount of sweet and spice. I also had the infused iced tea and they complimented my meal perfectly. The staff was so friendly and nice can't wait to come back here!
Natalie Porkman was vegan and yummy. Loved it.

Lots of vegetarian options.

I came here for lunch when I visited DC. I originally planned to eat at Copy Cat on H Street but it wasn't open til 5pm so I opened Yelp app & the name Pow Pow caught my eye. Not sure what type of Asian inspired food they were serving but pictures online looked enticing and prices were only $9 to $10 bucks.  I started with the Trolley Fries with Pulled Pork (fries with kimchi, cheddar, Korean ketchup, spicy mayo, cilantro). Oh my! I didn't expect this to be a meal in itself but it sure was heavenly. I simply couldn't resist the perfectly crisp fries, melted cheese topped with juicy pulled pork. At this point, I was already full but I decided to order a bowl. Might as well cause I was only in town for the weekend anyway :)  I got the Yoga Dragon bowl (mock fried chicken in peanut sauce, black beans, veggies, spicy nut crumbles drizzled with cucumber-lime & sriracha sauce). I only had a few bites but it was very tasty. I took the rest home and ate it the following day and it was still pretty yummy. This place is a great option for fresh made to order lunch other than typical fast food chain without breaking the bank.
You got to try this place, the Asian fusion concept is well done
Tasty vittles. The rice/quinoa mix is super tasty. Veggie and omnivore options available.

Food was okay. I got the Natalie Porkman. While the seitan was really tasty, the sour taste of the kimchi and pickled onions did not go well with it. I'll have to try another option next time.  On another note, the staff was very friendly!
Fantastic time meeting Jarobi White, his bowl was the bomb! They had samples and cool decor.

I had heard through the grapevine that Chef Jarobi White was coming through this restaurant, and I took it upon myself to make the hike from the MD burbs to go see him.  H St is mostly unexplored territory for me.  Not only is it 1.5 miles from the two closest metro stations, but somehow the locals are always heavily populating the strip of bars and restaurants, so parking can be a pain as well.  In this case, I was lucky enough to get a ride.  I arrived about 15 minutes after the official event began, and I was a bit surprised.  It was a rather small restaurant... could maybe fit 20-30 people max to be seated comfortably.  Even so, I walked up to the big menu so I could figure out what I was going to get.  Some of the choices looked really interesting, and I love that they had something with "Midnight Marauders" in the name.  They also had an egg roll with banana and nutella... I was beyond tempted to get that, but I needed something healthier.  I was going to get the Purity Bowl, but then I saw that they had "Jarobi specials" since he was coming through.  I decided that they wouldn't be around again, so I got the "Beets, Honey and Rice" bowl.  It had pickled onions, beet drizzle, Taiwanese fried honey chicken, and some other things in it.  I was surprised at how filling it was!  My chicken was real, but I saw that they have several vegetarian and vegan options.  I really enjoyed myself at this spot.  I got to meet Jarobi, take a picture with him, vibe to a lot of old school hip-hop, and just chill.  I absolutely have to take my sister... maybe I can make her drive, haha.
The food is the BOMB diggity......very trendy....and employees are fresh to death...
Love Pow Pow. Great, tasty food and fun ambience. Try the trolley fries, they're epic!
Absolutely love it and super healthy!
Good food. I liked the music, but it was too loud to talk to the group at out table.  Also, the stairs are very steep to climb up to the second floor restaraunt.
Great food options
Very basic fast casual experience that tasted bland for too high a price.  You will get your servings of veggies that day though.

Interesting food to say the least, kinda like a Chipotle but way healthier. The meals are all programmed with specific flavors so you can't mix and match BUT we had the supafly sukka (good but a but spicy), tokoyo robots which was the best, and a mock chicken something...the mock chicken and sentai are interesting and veryyyyyyy good. I truly suggest you give this place a shot! Filling and good taste!
Uniquely good food
Wu Banger. Amazing! New favorite place for lunch.
Flavorful vegan friendly options. The customer service is great!
Amazing place, super healthy and really unique and delicious. Go here as much as I can. WuBanger is the best option for sure

This is by far my favorite restaurant on H street. Kinda hidden behind the 13th & H trolley stop, just enough to keep it a secret still. Which I LOVE! Probably not for much longer though. I post up with my laptop a couple days a week and get their Wu-Banger bowl. Just starting serving killer cold brew coffee too. Keep it up guys!
After seeing good reviews, this was a disappointment. I got the bowl with orange chicken, and it did not make my stomach happy. Maybe I should've tried the eggroll...

Very good food and drinks. Would definitely go there again.

My sister and I were blown away. Awesome food and knowledgeable it was great
Awesome place. Get a small yoga dragon and small egg roll for a Devine meal.
rice was good but too much vegi (90%) and things don't get along that well

The burrito-sized egg rolls are great, and the shop has a cool, hole-in-the-wall atmosphere with interesting wall art. Meals usually take about 5 minutes to serve after ordering.  There are also very good vegetarian options.  My only complaint is that the service can occasionally be disorganized, ie, they may get part of your order wrong.

My business partner and I stopped in and thought the food was definitely 5 star.  It was really great and very innovative and different. I dinged it a little bit with 4 stars because I wanted a beer and they didn't have any alcohol yet. The people working there were great people as were the owners. Price was very competitive for what you got. Would recommend this place highly and intend to go back with my wife.
Just plain delicious

High prices (as others have said). I can't say I could recommend the entire menu (hence the 3 stars) mostly because the swords (and mini swords) kind of feel as though they are missing something - either a more interesting wrap or a better tasting sauce to dip them in).  I feel like this place has potential after having the trolley fries - I am just not super excited to try the rest of the menu after ordering a few of the swords and having them be pretty underwhelming for how much they cost.
Best bowls on H street.
Awesome food, great choices. Bit pricey, but definitely worth the splurge. Wu-Banger is my go to, but the others are just as delicious.
Really great veggie choices
Definitely go for one of the giant egg rolls!
Prices are a bit steep but the food is good. Pretty good portions. Fresh ingredients.

vegan friendly, but you have to work at it. not all the ingredients are labeled on the menu or readily accessible, so you can finagle a vegan bowl with some modifications. once that is out o the way, the food is good and the candied cashews …

Creative fast-casual food.  The prices are a bit steep - they need to be lowered by $1-$2 per dish.  Food-wise, the Trolley fries are fantastic.  The bowls are a little hit-or-miss - some are better than others (the chicken caesar one is quite good).  The egg rolls are quite unique and fun to share with a friend or two.
Prices are a bit high but this is the best Asian fusion place on H-Street I think. Unique options and I love their take on things.
Food amazing !!!!!!

With the fast casual movement in full force, restaurants need to think of unique offerings to stay relevant the latest DC fad is burrito sized anything. We have Buredo serving burrito sized sushi (I still can't bring myself to do it) and now we have burrito sized egg/spring rolls thanks to our newest neighbor on H Street NE, Pow Pow.  My Monday night dinner buddy and I were skeptical when we saw their menu- three burrito sized egg rolls and salads. What if we didn't like anything on the menu? We had to take the risk.  My buddy ordered the Purity Bowl and he LOVED it. He's a chef on the side and thinks most things are just "meh" so when he loves something, you know it's top notch. I ordered the Midnight Marauder, a burrito sized egg roll filled with steak, cheddar, onion kimchi, and napa cabbage. It was simple, but AMAZING! It comes with chipotle mayo (ask for seconds of that- you'll need it!) and it really brought out the flavors. It comes in two healthy portions and it's not overly greasy like other egg rolls and it filled me up as a whole meal! Wow. I will crave the Midnight Marauder.  The restaurant is right off the tram line in the middle of H Street NE. It's set up like a fast casual restaurant going through a line and picking from both booth and window seating.  The only things that prevented it from getting a five star review was the service. Even though it's a fast casual restaurant, it took 20 minutes for us to get our food. Also, the soda is $4 so ask for a cup for water (It's free!).

Everything I've had so far is really, really good.  Lots of complex, Korean-inspired flavors—giant egg rolls are basically sandwiches, but also a perfectly crispy egg roll.  So much yums.  I went twice today, and already know I will be here regularly.  I am definitely hooked.
The KTown is all the Noms! And then try the Wubanger. Sharkey's design makes it the best looking joint on Hst!  The taste is amazing and gluten free fried chicken is heavenly.
